channel.title: CVE Feed for NetApp -- all
channel.description: The latest CVEs for NetApp -- all products

item.title: CVE-2018-5498|2024-08-05T05:40:50.572Z -- netapp -- clustered%20data%20ontap
item.description: Clustered Data ONTAP versions 9.0 through 9.4 are susceptible to a vulnerability which allows remote authenticated attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) in NFS and SMB environments. Exploitation of this vulnerability will allow a remote authenticated attacker to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) on affected versions of clustered Data ONTAP configured for multiprotocol access.

item.title: CVE-2018-5496|2024-08-05T05:40:49.836Z -- netapp -- data%20ontap%20operating%20in%207-mode
item.description: Data ONTAP operating in 7-Mode versions prior to 8.2.5P2 are susceptible to a vulnerability which discloses sensitive information to an unauthorized user.

item.title: CVE-2018-5497|2024-08-05T05:40:50.503Z -- netapp -- clustered%20data%20ontap
item.description: Clustered Data ONTAP versions prior to 9.1P16, 9.3P10 and 9.4P5 are susceptible to a vulnerability which discloses sensitive information to an unauthorized user.

item.title: CVE-2018-5490|2024-08-05T05:40:50.508Z -- netapp -- clustered%20data%20ontap
item.description: Read-Only export policy rules are not correctly enforced in Clustered Data ONTAP 8.3 Release Candidate versions and therefore may allow more than "read-only" access from authenticated SMBv2 and SMBv3 clients. This behavior has been resolved in the GA release. Customers running prior release candidates (RCs) are requested to update their systems to the NetApp Data ONTAP 8.3 GA release.

item.title: CVE-2019-17272|2024-08-05T01:33:17.328Z -- netapp -- ontap%20select%20deploy%20administration%20utility
item.description: All versions of ONTAP Select Deploy administration utility are susceptible to a vulnerability which when successfully exploited could allow an administrative user to escalate their privileges.

item.title: CVE-2018-5488|2024-08-05T05:40:50.644Z -- netapp -- santricity%20products
item.description: NetApp SANtricity Web Services Proxy versions 1.10.x000.0002 through 2.12.X000.0002 and SANtricity Storage Manager 11.30.0X00.0004 through 11.42.0X00.0001 ship with the Java Management Extension Remote Method Invocation (JMX RMI) service bound to the network, and are susceptible to unauthenticated remote code execution.

item.title: CVE-2018-5487|2024-08-05T05:40:49.837Z -- netapp -- oncommand%20unified%20manager%20for%20linux
item.description: NetApp OnCommand Unified Manager for Linux versions 7.2 through 7.3 ship with the Java Management Extension Remote Method Invocation (JMX RMI) service bound to the network, and are susceptible to unauthenticated remote code execution.

item.title: CVE-2018-5489|2024-08-05T05:40:49.816Z -- netapp -- 7-mode%20transition%20tool
item.description: NetApp 7-Mode Transition Tool allows users with valid credentials to access functions and information which may have been intended to be restricted to administrators or privileged users. 7MTT versions below 2.0 do not enforce user authorization rules on file information and status that it has previously collected. The released version of 7MTT has been updated to maintain and verify authorization rules for file information, status and utilities.

item.title: CVE-2019-17274|2024-08-05T01:33:17.371Z -- netapp -- netapp%20fas%208300%2F8700%20and%20aff%20a400%20baseboard%20management%20controller
item.description: NetApp FAS 8300/8700 and AFF A400 Baseboard Management Controller (BMC) firmware versions 13.x prior to 13.1P1 were shipped with a default account enabled that could allow unauthorized arbitrary command execution via local access.

item.title: CVE-2018-5481|2024-08-05T05:40:49.842Z -- netapp -- oncommand%20unified%20manager%20for%207-mode%20%28core%20package%29
item.description: OnCommand Unified Manager for 7-Mode (core package) prior to 5.2.4 uses cookies that lack the secure attribute in certain circumstances making it vulnerable to impersonation via man-in-the-middle (MITM) attacks.

item.title: CVE-2018-5485|2024-08-05T05:40:49.821Z -- netapp -- oncommand%20unified%20manager%20for%20windows
item.description: NetApp OnCommand Unified Manager for Windows versions 7.2 through 7.3 are susceptible to a vulnerability which could lead to a privilege escalation attack.

item.title: CVE-2019-17275|2024-08-05T01:33:17.334Z -- netapp -- oncommand%20cloud%20manager
item.description: OnCommand Cloud Manager versions prior to 3.8.0 are susceptible to arbitrary code execution by remote attackers.

item.title: CVE-2019-17273|2024-08-05T01:33:17.415Z -- netapp -- e-series%20santricity%20os%20controller%20software
item.description: E-Series SANtricity OS Controller Software version 11.60.0 is susceptible to a vulnerability which allows an attacker to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) in IPv6 environments.

item.title: CVE-2018-5495|2024-08-05T05:40:50.566Z -- netapp -- storagegrid%20webscale
item.description: All StorageGRID Webscale versions are susceptible to a vulnerability which could permit an unauthenticated attacker to communicate with systems on the same network as the StorageGRID Webscale Admin Node via HTTP or to take over services on the Admin Node.

item.title: CVE-2018-5486|2024-08-05T05:40:49.837Z -- netapp -- oncommand%20unified%20manager%20for%20linux
item.description: NetApp OnCommand Unified Manager for Linux versions 7.2 though 7.3 ship with the Java Debug Wire Protocol (JDWP) enabled which allows unauthorized local attackers to execute arbitrary code.

item.title: CVE-2018-5492|2024-08-05T05:40:49.827Z -- netapp -- e-series%20santricity%20os%20controller%20software
item.description: NetApp E-Series SANtricity OS Controller Software 11.30 and later version 11.30.5 is susceptible to unauthenticated remote code execution.

item.title: CVE-2018-5499|2024-08-05T05:40:50.595Z -- netapp -- atto%20fibrebridge%207500n
item.description: ATTO FibreBridge 7500N firmware version 2.95 is susceptible to a vulnerability which allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS).

item.title: CVE-2018-5482|2024-08-05T05:40:49.840Z -- netapp -- snapcenter%20server
item.description: NetApp SnapCenter Server prior to 4.1 does not set the secure flag for a sensitive cookie in an HTTPS session which can allow the transmission of the cookie in plain text over an unencrypted channel.

item.title: CVE-2024-21993|2024-07-11T15:12:49.194Z -- netapp -- snapcenter
item.description: SnapCenter versions prior to 5.0p1 are susceptible to a vulnerability which could allow an authenticated attacker to discover plaintext credentials.

item.title: CVE-2024-21984|2024-07-05T17:20:57.011Z -- netapp -- storagegrid
item.description: StorageGRID (formerly StorageGRID Webscale) versions prior to 11.8 are susceptible to a difficult to exploit Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability. Successful exploit requires the attacker to know specific information about the target instance and trick a privileged user into clicking a specially crafted link. This could allow the attacker to view or modify configuration settings or add or modify user accounts.
